Iavan Pijoos, News24The aircraft that had crashed in Midrand. (Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Pretoria - Two people survived with minor injuries after a small aircraft crashed in Midrand on Wednesday morning, paramedics said.The aircraft was found lying upside-down in an open veld near the airport, ER24 spokesperson Werner Vermaak said.&ldquo;Two men, believed to be in their early thirties, were found walking around scene,&rdquo; Vermaak said.They sustained minor injuries.The incident happened at 04:00 on Wednesday morning.Both men were transported to Sunninghill Hospital for further assessment.The exact causes of the accident were not yet known. &nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.